CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1955, pg. 19 reads: "HIlltop Bungalow - An interesting adaptation of home construction to the natural contours of the site is the home of the Alvin Williams family on Iowa Street. Herbert Clark, of Ross Township, is the builders [sic]. The living room in rear presents a commanding view of the Cathedral of Learning and the Oakland Civic Center."
TitMainTitle: Newly constructed single story brick house of Alvin Williams with stone trim, single attached garage below house, and door with round window, 3034 Iowa Street
